In re BLUMBERG. (No. 2.) (Supreme Court, Appellate Division, Second Department. February 23, 1912.) Appeal from Special Term, Kings County. Application by David Blumiberg for an order discharging a mechanic’s lien. From an order denying a motion to vacate an order for the discharge of the lien, and to reinstate the lien, Lena Greenbaum, assignee of the lien, appeals. Reversed, and motion to reinstate lien granted.

Argued before JENKS, P. J., and BURR, THOMAS, CARR, and WOODWARD, JJ.

Marshall Snyder, for appellant. Arthur G. Fuchs, for respondent. *778PER CURIAM.

Order reversed, with $10 costs and disbursements, and motion granted, with $10 costs, on authority of Matter of Blumberg (Appeal No. 1) 133 N. Y. Supp. 774, decided herewith.

BURR, J., not voting.
